edu.ncsu.csc216.simulation.environment

Interface EcoGrid

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Ecosystem

    public interface EcoGrid
    Behaviors of a rectangular grid. Each grid cell in the grid can contain an Item.
    Author:
    Jo Perry

      • findFirstEmptyNeighbor

        Location findFirstEmptyNeighbor(Location position,
                                int startDirection)
        Find the first cell in the grid that shares a border with the cell at the given position and that contains no Animal. Start looking in the given direction and continue clockwise around the cell.
        Parameters:
        position - the position of the animal that is looking for an empty neighbor
        startDirection. - Direction to start: 0 = west, 1 = north, 2 = east, 3 = south.
        Returns:
        the location for the first empty neighbor found, or null if none are found.
